Brazil Stock Movers: Anhanguera, Hypermarcas, OGX Petroleo & Gas

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-09-19T15:52:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/brazil-stock-movers-anhanguera-hypermarcas-ogx-petroleo-gas.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:06 a.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 1.5 percent to 56,359.55.  Anhanguera Educacional Participacoes SA (AEDU3)  (AEDU3 BS),
Brazil’s largest education company by market value, rose 1.5
percent to 25.19 reais as  Banco Santander  called its acquisition
of Uniban Group “strategically positive.” Valinhos, Brazil-
based Anhanguera yesterday said it agreed to buy Uniban Group
for 510.6 million reais ($287 million). Uniban consists of three
companies that own four Brazilian colleges.  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3 BS), the  oil
company  controlled by billionaire  Eike Batista , declined 2.3
percent to 11.73 reais on speculation that  Greece  may not
receive a payment that would help it avoid default, driving down
commodities. Crude for October delivery declined 2.8 percent to
$85.53 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange .  Hypermarcas SA (HYPE3)  (HYPE3 BS), the Brazilian consumer-products
company that made 12 acquisitions since the start of 2010, lost
4.5 percent to 11.43 reais after it was cut to “neutral” from
“buy” at Banco BTG Pactual SA. BTG analysts led by Fabio Monteiro lowered their 12-month stock price estimate on
Hypermarcas to 15 reais from 21 reais, writing that “ongoing
integration process and new commercial policies in recent
quarters raise uncertainties over top line growth recovery.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
